        "text": "Another of Jean-Pierre Mocky's irreverent and deeply interesting tonal mish-mashes – part sports culture satire, part lunatic home invasioner, part future dystopian warning.\n\nStarting with a simple football match, a penalty decision riles the travelling legion of fans of the ‘Yellow and Blacks’, so much so that they decide to hunt down the referee and in an ever-escalating game of overtly stylized genre beats. A simple film about the fanaticism of the sports fan soon degenerates into an almost Rollerball-esque horror film, as the referee and his girlfriend are hunted through an empty shopping centre, trapped in their barricaded futuristic looking apartment with the villainous horde resorting to extreme means to break in, and culminating in a bizarre car chase…"
